{"TopicId":217396,"ForumId":36,"TopicTitle":"[1.12.x] ZTheme v1.1.3 - A dark theme for KSP (2024-02-27)","CreatedByName":"zapsnh","CreatedById":229115,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-05-27T14:45:17Z","PageNum":6,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"OnlyLightMatters","CreatedById":204296,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-07-13T15:05:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi everyone. After months not playing KSP1 I\u0027ve been back to business \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0I think A6/FM1 was an incentive after all. Thank god she took off, we can finally move forward here on the european\u0027s spaceport.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EOf course I am playing with ZTheme and a year later when I gave a very modest hand I have fresh eyes on the subject. Here are my thoughts, complains and sometimes suggestions. I try to being as constructive as possible,\u00A0\u00A0I apologize if my comments are a bit blunt. I\u0027m not a native English speaker and I don\u0027t always know how to present criticism properly. These should be considered as a few remarks regarding an astonishing and enormous work provided bu the author!\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E1- Navball Main Marker\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EThis is by far the most annoying point to me because it has a huge impact on my gameplay. The current shape of the marker is\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022gtwo.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002230.77\u0022 height=\u002236\u0022 width=\u0022117\u0022 src=\u0022https://zupimages.net/up/24/28/gtwo.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nTo understand my issue you will have to watch a few seconds of the following video of a RDV tutorial I made :\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 title=\u0022Kerbals need help! Rendezvous Tutorial - APSA #08 - KSP KSRSS 2.5 Kerbalism\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/M3BrPZePK90?start=610\u0026amp;feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs you can see when I perform a RDV, I make some refinements of my trajectory so that I always end up close to my target. The lines of the main marker are a strong help to help with performing these actions. But they can only help if there are aligned with the center of the marker.\u003Cbr\u003E\nSo in my games I have updated the icon with this one \u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022rb1q.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002230.77\u0022 height=\u002236\u0022 width=\u0022117\u0022 src=\u0022https://zupimages.net/up/24/28/rb1q.png\u0022\u003E\u00A0It is possible that I\u0027ll end up with thiner lines and a smaller central point.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E2- Navball Green and Red zones\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nGiven the general flat design of the theme, outlines are not very cohesive.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022p7ho.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002281.38\u0022 height=\u0022236\u0022 width=\u0022290\u0022 src=\u0022https://zupimages.net/up/24/28/p7ho.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have currently no proposal to make, I started to rework the whole thing with Inkscape but there is a lot of work to be done.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E3- Reputation in career mode\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022fuun.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u00224.69\u0022 height=\u002224\u0022 width=\u0022512\u0022 src=\u0022https://zupimages.net/up/24/28/fuun.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think there is too many information here. I have started the design of a cleaner image, not satisfying to my taste at this point.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00223htd.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u00224.69\u0022 height=\u002224\u0022 width=\u0022512\u0022 src=\u0022https://zupimages.net/up/24/28/3htd.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is way too simple, the 100 indications have to be present in some way. But beyong being good looking, this image is not very critical for gameplay purposes, we really don\u0027t care that much to our reputation when playing in Career mode.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E4- Exit Icons\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA few icons still have a red outline. Outlines IMHO are not welcome in this theme.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey currently are\u003Cimg alt=\u002264ed.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022100.00\u0022 height=\u0022256\u0022 width=\u0022256\u0022 src=\u0022https://zupimages.net/up/24/28/64ed.png\u0022\u003E, I am playing with\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022zq5q.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022100.00\u0022 height=\u0022256\u0022 width=\u0022256\u0022 src=\u0022https://zupimages.net/up/24/28/zq5q.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E5- Altitude\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0I don\u0027t know whether we need shadows on the white lines.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExisting\u003Cimg alt=\u0022uugi.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002220.00\u0022 height=\u002231\u0022 width=\u0022155\u0022 src=\u0022https://zupimages.net/up/24/28/uugi.png\u0022\u003E\u00A0my file\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u00226aww.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002220.00\u0022 height=\u002231\u0022 width=\u0022155\u0022 src=\u0022https://zupimages.net/up/24/28/6aww.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E6- Game Icons (This is my fault, they are my work)\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe don\u0027t see them that much so they are far from being an issue. But if we follow through with the approach, we should get rid off as many as outlines as possible.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExisting is\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022ScienceSandbox_normal128x128.png?ex=6693\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022100.00\u0022 height=\u0022128\u0022 width=\u0022128\u0022 src=\u0022https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1261024633767858208/1261032220769124383/ScienceSandbox_normal128x128.png?ex=66937586\u0026amp;is=66922406\u0026amp;hm=1328cf678b99355ffa2897520263b8355c443b95c147d94fc4f6d66cc0dc3f15\u0026amp;\u0022\u003E\u00A0Could be something lighter like\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022ScienceSandbox_normal128x128.png?ex=6693\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022100.00\u0022 height=\u0022128\u0022 width=\u0022128\u0022 src=\u0022https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1261024633767858208/1261699268297625621/ScienceSandbox_normal128x128.png?ex=6693e882\u0026amp;is=66929702\u0026amp;hm=9c2ca4c192dc042a941d90d3131ff589a650b6df8fce63098086605c508da2b1\u0026amp;\u0022\u003E. Work in progress.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EFeel free to comment on the proposals and start a dialogue here !\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAll my work is available at\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/OnlyLightMatters/SrcZTheme\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/OnlyLightMatters/SrcZTheme\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222024-07-14T12:23:41Z\u0022 title=\u002207/14/2024 12:23  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 hr\u0022\u003E2 hours ago\u003C/time\u003E by OnlyLightMatters\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"zapsnh","CreatedById":229115,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-07-14T01:04:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224407395\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022217396\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221720883142\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022204296\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022OnlyLightMatters\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, OnlyLightMatters said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E6- Game Icons (This is my fault, they are my work)\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe don\u0027t see them that much so they are far from being an issue. But if we follow through with the approach, we should get rid off as many as outlines as possible.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExisting is\u00A0\u003Ca data-fileid=\u0022undefined\u0022 href=\u0022https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1261024633767858208/1261032220769124383/ScienceSandbox_normal128x128.png?ex=66937586\u0026amp;is=66922406\u0026amp;hm=1328cf678b99355ffa2897520263b8355c443b95c147d94fc4f6d66cc0dc3f15\u0026amp;\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022ScienceSandbox_normal128x128.png?ex=6693\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022100.00\u0022 height=\u0022128\u0022 width=\u0022128\u0022 src=\u0022https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1261024633767858208/1261032220769124383/ScienceSandbox_normal128x128.png?ex=66937586\u0026amp;is=66922406\u0026amp;hm=1328cf678b99355ffa2897520263b8355c443b95c147d94fc4f6d66cc0dc3f15\u0026amp;\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0Could be something lighter like\u00A0\u003Ca data-fileid=\u0022undefined\u0022 href=\u0022https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1261024633767858208/1261699268297625621/ScienceSandbox_normal128x128.png?ex=6693e882\u0026amp;is=66929702\u0026amp;hm=9c2ca4c192dc042a941d90d3131ff589a650b6df8fce63098086605c508da2b1\u0026amp;\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022ScienceSandbox_normal128x128.png?ex=6693\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022100.00\u0022 height=\u0022128\u0022 width=\u0022128\u0022 src=\u0022https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1261024633767858208/1261699268297625621/ScienceSandbox_normal128x128.png?ex=6693e882\u0026amp;is=66929702\u0026amp;hm=9c2ca4c192dc042a941d90d3131ff589a650b6df8fce63098086605c508da2b1\u0026amp;\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E. Work in progress.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe icons should probably have a thicker outline since they are much smaller in-game. (at least at 100% scaling)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Fizzlebop Smith","CreatedById":227275,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-07-14T01:43:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI like the top two selection for exit. Current \u0026amp; Solid Red.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso want to say thank you. This is my favorite UI skin so far.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"OnlyLightMatters","CreatedById":204296,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-07-14T12:27:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224407498\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022217396\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221720919077\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022229115\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022zapsnh\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 hours ago, zapsnh said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe icons should probably have a thicker outline since they are much smaller in-game. (at least at 100% scaling)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExcellent point, I have to test them in a 1920x1200 100% UI configuration.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLast proposal \u003Cspan\u003E:\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022bopq.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022100.00\u0022 height=\u0022128\u0022 width=\u0022128\u0022 src=\u0022https://zupimages.net/up/24/28/bopq.png\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022ymqa.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022100.00\u0022 height=\u0022128\u0022 width=\u0022128\u0022 src=\u0022https://zupimages.net/up/24/28/ymqa.png\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022xknk.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022100.00\u0022 height=\u0022128\u0022 width=\u0022128\u0022 src=\u0022https://zupimages.net/up/24/28/xknk.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EI don\u0027t like the last one, I can\u0027t figure out a simple concept that I can illustrate with one only object/symbol.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222024-07-14T12:31:37Z\u0022 title=\u002207/14/2024 12:31  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 hr\u0022\u003E2 hours ago\u003C/time\u003E by OnlyLightMatters\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}